## Why This Is Asked
Tests practical troubleshooting of containerized workloads on Linux, focusing on cgroup throttling and IO path diagnosis under backup windows.

## Key Concepts
- cgroups v1/v2 quotas
- IO throttling and blkio
- container-process mapping
- cpuset CPU/memory isolation

## Code Example
```javascript
// Read quotas for a cgroup path
const fs = require('fs');
const p = process.argv[2];
try {
  const cpu = fs.readFileSync(`${p}/cpu.max`, 'utf8').trim();
  const mem = fs.readFileSync(`${p}/memory.max`, 'utf8').trim();
  console.log(`CPU_MAX=${cpu} MEM_MAX=${mem}`);
} catch (e) {
  console.log('Quota files not found');
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you automate across all containers?
- How handle dynamic quota changes during backups?

## Why This Is Asked
Tests practical debugging of ephemeral ports and TIME_WAIT behavior under bursts, a common production pitfall for web services.

## Key Concepts
- Ephemeral port range, TIME_WAIT backlog, FD limits
- net.ipv4.tcp_tw_reuse and ip_local_port_range
- Observability: ss, /proc, ulimit, and service limits

## Code Example
```javascript
// Quick Node snippet to count TIME_WAIT entries from /proc/net/tcp
const fs = require('fs');
const lines = fs.readFileSync('/proc/net/tcp','utf8').split('\n').slice(1);
const count = lines.filter(l => l.trim().split(/\s+/)[3] === '06').length;
console.log(`TIME_WAIT sockets: ${count}`);
```

## Why This Is Asked
This question tests practical ability to diagnose CPU throttling from container quotas, a common production issue requiring knowledge of both container management and Linux cgroups.

## Key Concepts
- Linux cgroups CPU controller (quota, period, throttling metrics)
- Container resource isolation through quotas vs. CPU pinning
- Monitoring tools: top, pidstat, cpu.stat for observability
- Safe quota adjustments without disrupting services

## Code Example
```javascript
// Example: Read cgroup CPU quotas and stats for Docker container
const fs = require('fs');
const containerId = process.argv[2];

function readCgroupStat(containerId) {
  const cgroupPath = `/sys/fs/cgroup/cpu/docker/${containerId}`;
  const quota = fs.readFileSync(`${cgroupPath}/cpu.cfs_quota_us`, 'utf8').trim();
  const period = fs.readFileSync(`${cgroupPath}/cpu.cfs_period_us`, 'utf8').trim();
  const stat = fs.readFileSync(`${cgroupPath}/cpu.stat`, 'utf8').trim();

  return { quota, period, stat };
}

console.log(readCgroupStat(containerId));
```
